1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Watch on kisskh.me

2
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:39,970
[Moonlight]

3
00:01:40,140 --> 00:01:43,000
[Episode 10]
Watch on kisskh.me

4
00:01:43,030 --> 00:01:45,590
Being a commercial writer isn't that bad.

5
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:47,190
Without a slight desire

6
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:48,190
to write,

7
00:01:48,190 --> 00:01:50,310
you can't write anything popular at all.

8
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:51,550
Besides, I've read it.

9
00:01:51,550 --> 00:01:53,990
You really poured your heart
into this book.

10
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,300
Listen.

11
00:02:00,300 --> 00:02:02,870
Don't be fooled by Mr Zhou Chuan

12
00:02:02,870 --> 00:02:05,070
and think he is above you.

13
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:06,750
That fellow

14
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:08,990
is only good at twisting words.

15
00:02:08,990 --> 00:02:09,950
You'd better not

16
00:02:09,950 --> 00:02:11,740
talk to him about life
or ambition whatsoever.

17
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:12,940
He's toxic.

18
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:16,950
I really want to record all these

19
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:18,070
and send it to Zhou Chuan.

20
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:20,310
Oh, don't.

21
00:02:20,630 --> 00:02:22,910
Let's just continue eating, Mr Jiang.

22
00:02:39,579 --> 00:02:41,780
Why isn't she back yet?

23
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,450
[Corner Bookstore]

24
00:02:52,829 --> 00:02:54,060
[Hi, we have received your submission
under science fiction genre.]

25
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:55,380
[But it's far from what we imagined.
Hope we can collaborate in the next one.]

26
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:02,950
Here's your coffee.

27
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:04,220
Thanks.

28
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:07,300
[The Long Goodbye]

29
00:03:07,660 --> 00:03:08,580
[The Long Goodbye]

30
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:18,670
[You like this book too?]

31
00:03:20,990 --> 00:03:21,710
[Yes, I do.]

32
00:03:22,670 --> 00:03:23,550
[Why?]

33
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:28,070
[It's supposed to be a detective fiction]

34
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:30,110
[but my mind is not only on the mystery.]

35
00:03:30,110 --> 00:03:31,710
[I'm more intrigued]

36
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:33,380
[by the characters]

37
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,310
[and how they cross paths.]

38
00:03:36,110 --> 00:03:38,030
[It's exactly Raymond's charm.]

39
00:03:38,630 --> 00:03:40,030
[I like this book too.]

40
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,870
[Every character]

41
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:43,630
[has his or her own story.]

42
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:45,550
[Moreover his writing]

43
00:03:45,550 --> 00:03:46,670
[is known for one unique feature.]

44
00:03:46,670 --> 00:03:48,710
[He uses simple]

45
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:49,910
[but very precise words]

46
00:03:49,910 --> 00:03:50,980
[to illustrate]

47
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:52,510
[the deepest thoughts of his characters.]

48
00:03:52,910 --> 00:03:53,950
[Very intense.]

49
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:55,550
[How I wish]

50
00:03:55,550 --> 00:03:57,190
[my novels are as good as his.]

51
00:03:58,350 --> 00:03:59,390
[You're a writer?]

52
00:03:59,390 --> 00:04:00,030
[Yes.]

53
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:01,950
[I write mostly]

54
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:03,230
[detective mysteries.]

55
00:04:03,630 --> 00:04:05,150
[I'm an editor.]

56
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:06,030
[Really?]

57
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:07,380
[Yes.]

58
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:10,190
[If you don't mind,]

59
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:11,830
[I can look at your novel.]

60
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:13,470
[Sure.]

61
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:16,310
[I'm Jiang Yu Cheng.]

62
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:17,790
[I'm Gu Bai Zhi.]

63
00:04:25,790 --> 00:04:27,750
Can I help you?

64
00:04:29,550 --> 00:04:30,430
No, it's fine.

65
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:56,030
[I bought these couple watches
when I got married.]

66
00:04:56,470 --> 00:04:58,310
[I'm thinking of saving them]

67
00:04:58,310 --> 00:05:01,500
[as a wedding gift to you and Xiao Jiang.]

68
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:03,909
[No, Ms Liu.]

69
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:06,190
[Mr Lin left them for you.]

70
00:05:07,910 --> 00:05:09,670
[I'll be seeing him soon.]

71
00:05:09,670 --> 00:05:11,830
[Why do I need these?]

72
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:16,430
[My only hope is that
you and Xiao Jiang are together.]

73
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:20,150
[I can then leave in peace.]

74
00:05:20,910 --> 00:05:22,870
[What are you talking about?]

75
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:44,250
[Gu Bai Zhi]

76
00:05:51,670 --> 00:05:52,470
Hello?

77
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:58,310
Hello?

78
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,590
Hello?

79
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:21,630
Just two hours later

80
00:06:21,630 --> 00:06:22,990
and you got yourself this drunk?

81
00:06:22,990 --> 00:06:23,870
Sis.

82
00:06:48,270 --> 00:06:49,190
What is it?

83
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:51,230
Jiang Yu Cheng.
Why didn't you pick up?

84
00:06:51,990 --> 00:06:52,909
[Are you done?]

85
00:06:52,909 --> 00:06:53,830
[It's just a contract.]

86
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:54,909
[Can you get it over with?]

87
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:56,750
I'm starving here.

88
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,900
I haven't eaten anything
after I finished writing.

89
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:00,830
Can you return my editor to me?

90
00:07:01,870 --> 00:07:03,430
Without Chu Li you'd starve?

91
00:07:05,470 --> 00:07:06,820
If Chu Li doesn't read the manuscript,

92
00:07:06,820 --> 00:07:08,260
I can't eat.

93
00:07:09,550 --> 00:07:10,780
Are you crazy?

94
00:07:10,780 --> 00:07:11,830
You kept her this late.

95
00:07:11,830 --> 00:07:13,070
You're the crazy one here.

96
00:07:13,070 --> 00:07:14,150
Not even a single reply.

97
00:07:14,150 --> 00:07:14,990
What happened?

98
00:07:14,990 --> 00:07:16,350
She left long ago.

99
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:18,310
If she didn't reply your message,
why don't you call her?

100
00:07:21,110 --> 00:07:21,830
Right.

101
00:07:27,310 --> 00:07:28,940
Er Gou, let's go.

102
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:30,550
Let's go for a walk.

103
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:32,150
Go for a walk.

104
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:33,310
Mr Zhou Chuan.
It's already so late.

105
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,950
You want to walk the dog now?

106
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:38,060
Who's walking the dog?

107
00:07:38,390 --> 00:07:39,630
Why didn't you reply my messages?

108
00:07:39,630 --> 00:07:40,710
What took you so long?

109
00:07:41,110 --> 00:07:42,310
You've been talking to him
so many times before.

110
00:07:42,310 --> 00:07:43,430
Aren't you done talking already?

111
00:07:44,390 --> 00:07:45,870
You've gotten attached to him?

112
00:07:47,030 --> 00:07:49,830
Mr Zhou Chuan.
What's brewing in that head now?

113
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:51,260
My phone died.

114
00:07:51,260 --> 00:07:53,430
I was just seeking advice from Mr Jiang

115
00:07:53,430 --> 00:07:54,590
on book publicity

116
00:07:54,590 --> 00:07:56,070
and ways to engage with

117
00:07:56,070 --> 00:07:57,710
physical booksellers.

118
00:07:58,670 --> 00:08:00,350
Why don't you ask me?

119
00:08:00,350 --> 00:08:01,390
You know about these too?

120
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:02,940
Are you kidding?

121
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:04,790
Of course I don't.

122
00:08:04,790 --> 00:08:05,550
Forget it.

123
00:08:05,550 --> 00:08:07,510
Let me make you some chrysanthemum tea

124
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:08,660
to calm you down.

125
00:08:08,870 --> 00:08:10,310
Make tea? I'm starving.

126
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:11,270
Make me something to eat.

127
00:08:14,380 --> 00:08:16,140
Have you sealed the deal

128
00:08:16,140 --> 00:08:17,510
on Jiang Yu Cheng's new book?

129
00:08:17,510 --> 00:08:19,070
Not yet.

130
00:08:19,470 --> 00:08:21,550
I want to wait

131
00:08:21,550 --> 00:08:23,940
for the birth of your masterpiece.

132
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:26,830
The printing house is going to
run out of paper very soon.

133
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:29,270
I didn't know you have a grudge
on the printing house.

134
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:33,630
Why are you so confident?

135
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,630
What got into you?

136
00:09:02,020 --> 00:09:03,150
[I've walked the dog.]

137
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:14,170
[Not Drama King, it's Saviour]

138
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:04,220
[What do I need you for?]

139
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:05,910
[Why aren't you back yet?]

140
00:09:05,910 --> 00:09:07,390
[Is there so much to talk about?]

141
00:09:07,390 --> 00:09:09,310
[I'm dying of hunger here.]

142
00:09:09,310 --> 00:09:10,430
[From now onwards,]

143
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:11,630
[every minute you take to reach home]

144
00:09:11,630 --> 00:09:13,510
[is causing you a hundred in rent.]

145
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:35,390
Mr Zhou Chuan.

146
00:09:36,110 --> 00:09:38,750
Book of Luo He God is going to print.

147
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:41,190
You must be nervous.

148
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:44,310
You should be the one feeling nervous.

149
00:09:44,790 --> 00:09:46,750
You went for a jog and
walked the dog at seven,

150
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,310
showered and set your hair at eight.

151
00:09:48,310 --> 00:09:50,190
Now you are here in time
for breakfast with me.

152
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:52,710
Isn't this a little too much for you?

153
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:55,070
I remember Mr Jiang say that

154
00:09:55,070 --> 00:09:56,190
once you are nervous,

155
00:09:56,190 --> 00:09:58,270
you'll try to become a normal person.

156
00:09:59,110 --> 00:10:01,100
You should be the one feeling nervous.

157
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,630
If this book failed to sell,

158
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:03,910
it won't be the end

159
00:10:03,910 --> 00:10:05,590
for Yuan Yue Publishing House and me.

160
00:10:05,590 --> 00:10:07,110
But without a doubt,

161
00:10:07,990 --> 00:10:10,190
you won't be my managing editor anymore.

162
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:14,350
[This person who gave me
my first contract]

163
00:10:14,350 --> 00:10:16,110
[will turn into]

164
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:17,310
[a stranger?]

165
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:18,870
Don't you think

166
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,950
I'm particularly virtuous and classy?

167
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:24,980
I'm done talking.

168
00:10:24,980 --> 00:10:26,030
I'm going to office now.

169
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:28,750
Why are you working on a Sunday?

170
00:10:30,190 --> 00:10:31,790
That's all thanks to you.

171
00:10:31,790 --> 00:10:32,780
You are simply

172
00:10:32,780 --> 00:10:34,190
too important to us.

173
00:10:34,190 --> 00:10:35,150
For the coming Sundays,

174
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:37,740
our entire department is working overtime
just for you.

175
00:10:37,740 --> 00:10:38,390
Goodbye.

176
00:10:46,430 --> 00:10:48,470
Out on weekends?

177
00:10:48,950 --> 00:10:50,500
You think this is a hotel?

178
00:10:57,910 --> 00:10:59,790
Sis, you're up.

179
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,670
Here.

180
00:11:03,950 --> 00:11:05,430
Why are you in my house?

181
00:11:07,190 --> 00:11:08,510
I called you yesterday.

182
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:09,830
The bartender answered

183
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:10,950
and told me you were drunk.

184
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:13,190
I immediately went to get you.

185
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,870
I'm sorry. Thanks.

186
00:11:17,870 --> 00:11:19,150
Do you still have a headache?

187
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:21,990
Take this pill.

188
00:11:38,090 --> 00:11:42,930
[Jiang Yu Cheng]

189
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:46,800
[Jiang Yu Cheng]

190
00:11:52,070 --> 00:11:53,660
Did I say anything last night

191
00:11:53,660 --> 00:11:54,910
that I'm not supposed to?

192
00:11:58,330 --> 00:12:04,400
[Reading Club]

193
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:13,420
[Reading. The City Never Sleeps]

194
00:12:33,260 --> 00:12:34,550
You're early.

195
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:36,030
Don't tell me you're here to buy books.

196
00:12:36,710 --> 00:12:38,510
I called you last night.

197
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:44,670
But when I answered,

198
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:46,550
you didn't say anything.

199
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:48,340
I guess you must have called by accident.

200
00:12:55,870 --> 00:12:56,870
Is there anything else?

201
00:12:58,590 --> 00:13:00,270
I visited Ms Liu.

202
00:13:00,270 --> 00:13:02,350
Her condition isn't too good.

203
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:03,790
Soon

204
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:05,030
she might even forget me.

205
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,270
Some things

206
00:13:12,670 --> 00:13:13,710
are better forgotten.

207
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:20,190
Can I ask you for a favour?

208
00:13:21,830 --> 00:13:22,710
Go ahead.

209
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:26,430
Can you accompany me to visit Ms Liu?

210
00:13:31,030 --> 00:13:33,150
[Yuan Yue Publishing House]

211
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:35,080
[Count down 15 days]

212
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:40,630
Mr Xia has gone out for a meeting today.

213
00:13:40,630 --> 00:13:42,550
I'll chair this meeting.

214
00:13:42,950 --> 00:13:43,710
Book of Luo He God

215
00:13:43,710 --> 00:13:45,870
is at the final phase.

216
00:13:46,310 --> 00:13:48,070
Chu Li,
circulation department informed that

217
00:13:48,070 --> 00:13:49,990
they lack of manpower.

218
00:13:49,990 --> 00:13:52,260
You'll have to write
the subscription letters.

219
00:13:53,190 --> 00:13:55,510
I think you should prepare
all the letters today

220
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:57,980
along with the information sheet

221
00:13:57,980 --> 00:13:59,670
so that the circulation department
can send them out

222
00:13:59,670 --> 00:14:01,590
to the various dealers
first thing next week.

223
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:02,430
No problem.

224
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:07,270
I think once we obtain the first

225
00:14:07,270 --> 00:14:09,710
subscription quantity from the dealers,

226
00:14:10,110 --> 00:14:11,270
we'll know

227
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:13,070
where this book stands

228
00:14:13,070 --> 00:14:14,670
in terms of sales potential.

229
00:14:15,430 --> 00:14:16,310
Chu Li.

230
00:14:16,430 --> 00:14:18,220
350 thousand

231
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:19,270
is the figure you set.

232
00:14:19,430 --> 00:14:20,540
Hence,

233
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:21,750
you have to work hard.

234
00:14:22,510 --> 00:14:23,550
[This figure]

235
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:26,510
[is now mine to bear.]

236
00:14:26,510 --> 00:14:29,070
Mr Liang has been very supportive.

237
00:14:29,070 --> 00:14:31,790
He visited major bookstores nationwide

238
00:14:31,790 --> 00:14:34,620
to obtain a two-week placement

239
00:14:34,620 --> 00:14:37,230
at 32 Guanghua Bookstores,

240
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:40,030
increasing the exposure
for Book of Luo He God.

241
00:14:40,030 --> 00:14:41,310
Guanghua Bookstore?

242
00:14:41,310 --> 00:14:42,670
Two-week placement?

243
00:14:42,980 --> 00:14:44,190
That's great.

244
00:14:45,470 --> 00:14:46,230
Chu Li.

245
00:14:46,590 --> 00:14:48,110
Don't get too excited just yet.

246
00:14:48,110 --> 00:14:50,670
Yuan Yue Publishing House may seem to be

247
00:14:50,670 --> 00:14:53,030
scrambling high and low

248
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:54,710
to achieve the 350 thousand mark

249
00:14:54,710 --> 00:14:56,030
that you set

250
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:57,350
for your book.

251
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:58,380
However,

252
00:14:58,380 --> 00:14:59,870
you're still a rookie

253
00:14:59,870 --> 00:15:01,190
who's too young

254
00:15:01,190 --> 00:15:02,430
and lack experience.

255
00:15:02,430 --> 00:15:05,510
350 thousand is an astronomical figure.

256
00:15:05,510 --> 00:15:06,750
I think

257
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:08,110
it's not possible at all.

258
00:15:10,430 --> 00:15:12,390
Well...

259
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:13,990
Chu Li is a newcomer.

260
00:15:13,990 --> 00:15:16,070
Not only her,

261
00:15:16,070 --> 00:15:17,150
Deputy Editor Miao,

262
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:18,870
even you can't achieve this figure too.

263
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:23,230
But having said that,

264
00:15:23,230 --> 00:15:26,100
with the support we get from
marketing and circulation departments,

265
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:27,030
who knows

266
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:28,510
we can really achieve it.

267
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,180
If a newcomer like Chu Li

268
00:15:30,180 --> 00:15:31,110
really achieve it,

269
00:15:31,110 --> 00:15:32,910
won't it be a slap in your face,
Deputy Editor Miao?

270
00:15:33,830 --> 00:15:34,550
Fine.

271
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:36,550
I'm not afraid then.

272
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:38,750
If this book can really

273
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:40,710
hit that figure,

274
00:15:40,710 --> 00:15:43,070
I'll give her my title.

275
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:44,750
Really?

276
00:15:44,950 --> 00:15:46,950
Alright then.
We'll work hard towards this.

277
00:15:48,310 --> 00:15:49,270
Alright.

278
00:15:58,630 --> 00:16:00,630
You're right on time, Mr Zhou Chuan.

279
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:01,790
I'm preparing the subscription letter

280
00:16:01,790 --> 00:16:03,950
for your Book of Luo He God.

281
00:16:03,950 --> 00:16:05,670
The publicity wordings used in the letter

282
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:07,990
may be used for the blurb
on the belly band later.

283
00:16:07,990 --> 00:16:08,580
Come over.

284
00:16:08,580 --> 00:16:10,270
